Key Match Events: Darius Garland scored 40 points in the fourth quarter to swing the game in favor of the Cavaliers
The Cavaliers came from behind to defeat the Toronto Raptors 132-126 after being down by 12 points in the third quarter
Post-Match Reflections: Cavaliers coach Kenny Atkinson praised Darius Garland's performance as the key factor in the win
Atkinson also mentioned that Garland's performance proves he should be in the All-Star game tier
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cavaliers extended their unbeaten streak to 12 games
